26/04/2005
PALE, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Bosnian Serb Zeljko Maljukan, considered a close associate of wartime Republika Srpska military commander Ratko Mladic, was arrested Monday (25 April) in a joint operation by NATO and EUFOR troops in Pale. 
NATO spokesman Dwight Mood said that the operation, which also included a search of houses and commercial premises, was conducted as part of NATO's mandate for tracking down war crimes suspects and breaking their support networks. 
Illegal weapons and munitions were found during the search. 
(Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 26/04/05; RTRS, PBS BiH, NTV Hayat - 25/04/05)
